review_blob: Pours an amber color, on the nose I smell citrus and a mixed fruit scent, taste is bitter hops at the mouth, then caramel at the throat. An OK IPA too much caramel flavor and not bitter enough for me.
This is a true Hop Bomb, one of the great double IPAs that i enjoy at least once a week.
The best stout out there! Roasted malt and chocolate with that alcohol burn at the end.
More hops than all the other Pale Ales that Ive tried, Id buy it again, cant wait to try some other beers by this brewery!
Another offering by Stone that I love! Alot of citrus in this beer with a puch of hops as well, it may be better than sex, but Ill get back to you on that one.
beer_name: Stone Stochasticity Project Grapefruit Slam IPA

review_blob: This beer is one of the greats made by the greatest brewery in the world, enough said.
Appearance is golden yellow with a thin white head and slight lacing.  Smell is of pineapple, biscuit, and grass.  Taste is of citrus, pineapple, with a bitter hop finish.  Its a great one!

Pours a hazy orange , it has a definite smell of citrus with a slight floral hint. Great hoppy bitterness flavor with a hint of lemon zest, lots of citrus in this beer, hops are not overpowering though.  One of the best IPAs oiut there!
poured a hazy orange with a decent frothy  white head, smells of pine and grapefruit.  Taste is of pine, pineapple, grapefruit with a slight taste of malt. Great everyday IPA
